immoral_action: Greg spray paints a memorial statue with with anti war quotes.

moral_action: John decides to find ways to differentiate his business from the new competitor and find a solid niche in the marketplace.
moral_consequence: Both businesses grow as customers choose which one fits their particular needs more.

immoral_action: John is privy to information that will shut down his new competitor and uses it to do so.
immoral_consequence: The competitor loses their life's work and spends the rest of their days trying to ruin John's business in revenge.

moral_action: Jon neatly folds the flag and lays it gently into the drawer.
moral_consequence: The school staff is grateful for Jon's careful volunteer work.

immoral_action: Jon crumples the flag up into a messy bundle and stuffs it in the drawer.
immoral_consequence: The school staff notice and are offended by Jon's actions.

moral_action: Hannah makes an announcement post on her social media accounts.
moral_consequence: Hannah's friends and family congratulate Hannah and share in her excitement.

immoral_action: Hannah announces her pregnancy at her sister's wedding reception.
immoral_consequence: Hannah's family are upset with Hannah for making her sister's wedding about her.

moral_action: Harry coaxes Tom into having several rounds of shots, and they order some bar food.
moral_consequence: Tom had an enjoyable time and feels fine the next day because the food absorbed some alcohol.

immoral_action: Harry spikes Tom's drinks with extra alcohol when he's not looking.
immoral_consequence: Tom has a really severe hangover the following day.

moral_action: Mary scoops up the dog poop into a bag and continues walking with her dog.
moral_consequence: Other people are able to walk along the beach and not worry about stepping in dog poop.

immoral_action: Mary lets her dog go to the bathroom in the sand.
immoral_consequence: A family walking down the beach steps in the dog poop.

moral_action: Winston yells wordlessly into the air as loudly as he can for several seconds.
moral_consequence: Winston feels better and is able to continue with his game but other players are bewildered.

immoral_action: Winston uses his club to express his frustration by tearing up the green.
immoral_consequence: Winston is forced to pay for the damage he caused and is banned from the golf course.

moral_action: Jackie turns the running water off and goes into the other room to answer the phone.
moral_consequence: Jackie is able to resume doing the dishes after her phone call without having wasted any water.

immoral_action: Jackie leaves the sink running and immediately runs over to the answer the phone.
immoral_consequence: Jackie's sink overflows and the kitchen floor is left covered in water.

moral_action: John declines the invitation from his coworker and instead takes his wife for the romantic dinner.
moral_consequence: John's wife is pleased with the change in their routine and reciprocates which leads to a revitalization of their marriage.

immoral_action: John tells his wife that hes going to visit his parents, but instead joins his coworker for a romantic meal and a night together.
immoral_consequence: John's wife finds out he cheated and leaves him.

moral_action: Ted tells his wife had some drinks with his coworkers.
moral_consequence: Ted's wife is unhappy that he got home later than usual but glad that he had a nice time with his coworkers.

immoral_action: Ted tells his wife he had to work late and doesn't tell her he went out for drinks.
immoral_consequence: Ted feels guilty about lying to his wife and has to tell more lies about working late.

moral_action: Kirby calmly explains that the toy wore out from being played with so much.
moral_consequence: Kirby's mother replaces the worn out toy at the store.

immoral_action: Kirby reacts poorly under pressure and screams that it wasn't his fault.
immoral_consequence: Kirby gets the new toy, but he's grounded for a week and thus can't actually play with it.

moral_action: Finley replies to his mom's text messages letting her know what time they will be done hanging out.
moral_consequence: Finley's mom is content knowing that her son is okay.

immoral_action: Finley ignores his mom's text messages and continues hanging out with his friends.
immoral_consequence: Finley's mom is worried that something is wrong with Finley.

moral_action: Matt explains to his wife that a couple of drinks after work does wonders for his stress level.
moral_consequence: Matt comes to an understanding with his wife about his drinking.

immoral_action: Matt smacks his wife in the face for calling him a drunkard.
immoral_consequence: Matt is arrested for domestic battery when his wife calls the police.

moral_action: Aaron invites Claire to party with his friends.
moral_consequence: Claire hits it off with Aaron's friends, and they begin hanging out as a group.

immoral_action: Aaron and his friends go out to a party without inviting Claire.
immoral_consequence: Sick of being alone all the time, Claire leaves Aaron.

moral_action: Derek offers to put a deposit down on an apartment for his mother and to go look at them with her.
moral_consequence: Derek's mother is touched by his offer and goes to find an apartment with his help.

immoral_action: Derek leaves a formal eviction notice on his mother's bedroom door before leaving for work.
immoral_consequence: Derek's mother feels that his actions were cold and hurtful and no longer speaks with him.

moral_action: Mary decides to give her mother a chance and agrees to meet with her.
moral_consequence: Mary is able to rebuild a relationship with her mother.

immoral_action: Mary decides to hold on to her anger and rejects her mother.
immoral_consequence: Mary later regrets that her child is missing out on knowing her grandmother.

moral_action: Joe is upfront about texting a female friend and lets her see the text to reassure her.
moral_consequence: Joe's wife is pleased he is being honest and feels satisfied.

immoral_action: Joe makes up that he is texting a male friend of his.
immoral_consequence: Joe's wife finds out who he was really texting and becomes even more jealous.

moral_action: James explains that his mother embarrassed him with people important to him.
moral_consequence: His mother apologizes and they hug afterwards.

immoral_action: James speaks an angry stream of profanity at his mother.
immoral_consequence: His mother just starts the same thing back at him.

moral_action: Jace takes a nap but makes sure to wake up in time to pick up Diane from work.
moral_consequence: Diane is happy to see Jace waiting for her when she walks out of her job.

immoral_action: Jace takes a nap and doesn't get up in time to pick up Diane from work.
immoral_consequence: Diane is annoyed that she has to get a ride home with a coworker.

moral_action: Troy tells Dana that he loves his mom very much, and he hasn't mentioned it because he thought it was obvious she'd come.
moral_consequence: Dana is relieved to hear that Troy's mom will come to their big day and that there's no problems in their relationship.

immoral_action: Troy tells Dana that his mother, and he don't talk and that he despises her and always has.
immoral_consequence: Dana is shocked to hear that Troy doesn't talk to his mom and wonders what's wrong with him.

moral_action: Don reads all the ads and the invites some he has a lot in common with on a date.
moral_consequence: Don has a wonderful date talking with his date about their shared interests.

immoral_action: Don sends invites the first person he reads about on a date.
immoral_consequence: Don has a bad date because the other person doesn't like Don.

moral_action: Frank goes to the movies with his friends.
moral_consequence: Frank becomes closer to his friends.

immoral_action: Frank spends the evening alone playing an online video game.
immoral_consequence: Later Frank feels lonely because he misses being around people.

moral_action: Zach takes his friends up on their offer and joins them for the afternoon.
moral_consequence: Zach has fun playing with his friends.

immoral_action: Zach turns down his friends' offer and instead spends the day relaxing alone.
immoral_consequence: Zach feel regenerated, but his friends are now a little bit more distant from him.

moral_action: Blanche invites her friends to the bar with her.
moral_consequence: Blanche's friend introduces her to a cute guy at the bar.

immoral_action: Blanche spends her weekend playing video games.
immoral_consequence: Blanche feels lonely because she misses her friends.

moral_action: Zach agrees to meet up with his friends.
moral_consequence: Zach's friends have a lot of fun hanging out with him, and they invite him out next time as well.

immoral_action: Zach declines his friends' invitation and stays home playing video games all weekend.
immoral_consequence: Zach's friends eventually stop inviting him out.

moral_action: Paul accepts the invitation from his friends and meets them at the bar.
moral_consequence: Paul's friends have a good time hanging out with Paul and invite him to a concert the next weekend.

immoral_action: Paul declines the invitation from his friends and spends the night watching TV at home.
immoral_consequence: Paul's friends think Paul isn't interested in hanging out with them, and they stop inviting him out on weekends.

moral_action: Timothy agrees to hang out with them for a while, and then goes back to his video game when he gets home.
moral_consequence: Timothy and his friends have a good time and hang out again later.

immoral_action: Timothy turns his buddy down and goes back to his video game.
immoral_consequence: Timothy's buddy doesn't bother to call him the next time they hang out.

moral_action: Henry decides to go out and hang with his friend for some time.
moral_consequence: Henry feels recharged and much better after spending time with his friend.

immoral_action: Henry decides to call a friend up and talk on the phone.
immoral_consequence: Henry still feels a bit lonely after the phone call because it wasn't very personal.

moral_action: Jared tells his team that he'll go out with them.
moral_consequence: Jared will be able to build better bonds with his work team.

immoral_action: Jared tells his team that he'll be going home after work.
immoral_consequence: Jared will not be able to build camaraderie with his work team.

moral_action: Lilly cooks a big meal in the kitchen and invites her friends over for dinner.
moral_consequence: Lilly cooking skills improve when her friends give her cooking tips as they eat.

immoral_action: Lilly tells her friends that she meet them today as she needs to watch her brother.
immoral_consequence: Lilly misses her friends.

moral_action: Len tells Randy he loves baseball and that he'll meet him at the diamond in the park.
moral_consequence: Randy is delighted and excited both to see his friend and to play some baseball.

immoral_action: Len tells Randy he hates baseball, and he doesn't want to come out, he'll stay home instead.
immoral_consequence: Randy is annoyed that Len doesn't want to hang out with him and play a fun sport and thinks Len is weird.

moral_action: Sally calls some friends to go out to the movies with.
moral_consequence: Sally has a great time watching the movie and hanging with friends.

immoral_action: Sally orders a movie online to watch by herself.
immoral_consequence: Sally finds the movie boring when watching alone.

moral_action: Sally talks to her partner and asks if there's anything she can do to help out with the project.
moral_consequence: Sally's partner thinks of something for Sally to do, so she can earn the credit for the project.

immoral_action: Sally goes to the teacher and tells the teacher that she did the work that her partner actually did.
immoral_consequence: Sally's partner finds out and proves to the teacher that they did all the work.

moral_action: Lev talks with his coworkers to see if they need help.
moral_consequence: He gets a project for next week that would have been tough and manages to get a head start.

immoral_action: Lev takes it easy all shift and doesn't ask for any work from anyone else.
immoral_consequence: Next week Lev gets hammered with work and regrets not getting a heads up.

moral_action: Mike works hard and seeks out challenges in order to think long term in his career.
moral_consequence: Mike is promoted six months later to a job that offers variety and more money.

immoral_action: Mike texts and plays games all day while horsing around with coworkers.
immoral_consequence: Mike is fired when his numbers do not meet the required quota.

moral_action: John declines the customer's offer stating that he just began at this job, and he's not disloyal.
moral_consequence: Carlos is happy to see John be a stand up person and is happy his choice to hire him has been validated in a way.

immoral_action: John tells the customer that of course he will accept the job as it's higher paying.
immoral_consequence: Carlos is angry that the training he just gave John is wasted and that he has to look for another employee.

moral_action: Lily goes to her boss and explains that she needs some time off.
moral_consequence: Lily is allowed to take an unpaid leave by her boss.

immoral_action: Lily quits her job on the spot and leaves immediately.
immoral_consequence: Lily gets a bad reference from her employer and has a hard time finding a new job.

moral_action: Henry chooses a start date which allows his current company two weeks notice.
moral_consequence: Henry feels like a good and responsible employee.

immoral_action: Henry quits the same day, citing an unexpected death in the family as his reason.
immoral_consequence: Henry feels guilty for lying about such a thing.

moral_action: Tony expresses concern about things which are negatively affecting his job in a private meeting with a supervisor.
moral_consequence: The manager liked one of his ideas and implements a change which makes the day a little easier.

immoral_action: Tony often complains to coworkers about policies and comments on angry customers.
immoral_consequence: Tony is not picked for promotions because management is concerned about his negative attitude.

moral_action: Jill decides to get up and go to work anyway, so she does.
moral_consequence: Jill has a great day at work and gets much more work done than she usually does.

immoral_action: Jill decides she doesn't feel like working today, so she doesn't go to work.
immoral_consequence: Jill gets her paycheck a week later and it's a day's smaller than usual.

moral_action: Despite not feeling his best, Joe eats a healthy breakfast, takes some aspirin and heads into work.
moral_consequence: Joe's boss see's that he doesn't feel well, but appreciates him coming in and sees Joe as someone who can be counted on.

immoral_action: Joe calls in sick to work, so he can stay home and take care of his hangover.
immoral_consequence: Joe comes across as an unreliable worker to his boss.

moral_action: Lucas calls his boss and tells him he won't go to the office today because he doesn't want anyone in the office to catch his bug.
moral_consequence: Lucas stays home and his colleague stays healthy.

immoral_action: Lucas goes to the office and doesn't mention feeling sick.
immoral_consequence: Lucas' colleague catches Lucas' virus.

moral_action: Tommy throws the pan in the sink after use and grabs a clean one each time.
moral_consequence: Tommy gets food moving quickly and hygienically out of the kitchen, and his boss is satisfied.

immoral_action: Tommy skips the important step of washing his pan after use, and just keeps cooking.
immoral_consequence: The next customer ends up getting food poisoning, and his boss gets sued.

moral_action: Craig asks a fellow teacher to sub his classes while he's at the doctor.
moral_consequence: The students are watched by an experienced teacher.

immoral_action: Craig assigns his classes busy work the day before, then goes to the appointment without notifying anyone.
immoral_consequence: The students go wild without a teacher and cause trouble.

moral_action: Gordon tells his wife that he's going golfing since he's taken a day off work today.
moral_consequence: Gordon's wife is happy to see Gordon utilizing some time off work to go do something relaxing.

immoral_action: Gordon tells his wife that he's going to work, it's just casual day, so he's taking advantage.
immoral_consequence: Gordon's wife later finds out he lied, and he had taken a day off work and is now suspicious of Gordon and insecure about him.

moral_action: Bianca puts in a two week notice and thanks the company for giving her an opportunity to work there.
moral_consequence: Bianca is able to get a job a few weeks later after receiving a good letter of recommendation from her previous company.

immoral_action: Bianca stands up one day and suddenly announces she is done with this job, and she walks out the door.
immoral_consequence: Bianca has trouble getting another job because her previous company gives her a bad recommendation.

moral_action: Steve waits until lunch time and goes to his car to take a nap.
moral_consequence: Steve comes back from his lunch break and is more productive than ever.

immoral_action: Steve gets down under his desk and takes a nap during work hours.
immoral_consequence: Steve is fired from his job when his boss sees that he isn't being productive.

moral_action: James tells his manager that he's going to lose his mind unless he gets some peace and quiet.
moral_consequence: The manager transfers James to stocking inventory in the deserted back room for a few hours.

immoral_action: James rips off his name tag, throws it at the bellowing customer, and storms out the door.
immoral_consequence: James is blacklisted at that store and by several other employers who know the owner.

moral_action: Tim finishes all his assigned paperwork although he has to stay at work late then he heads to the bar for a bit.
moral_consequence: Tim's boss is pleased with Tim's performance and gives Tim a promotion.

immoral_action: Tim leaves work early without finishing his paperwork and goes straight to the bar.
immoral_consequence: Tim's boss is angry that Tim for not getting the paperwork done and issues Tim a formal employee warning.

moral_action: Calvin makes sure to do his best work for the current client before starting the next job.
moral_consequence: Calvin's reputation begins to precede him, and he finds himself never short of work or clients.

immoral_action: Calvin takes shortcuts on the current job, so he can get to the next one faster.
immoral_consequence: Calvin shoddy work does not hold up and the original client sues him over it.

moral_action: Will says he'll pass on lunch but makes plans to meet up with them after work for a happy hour.
moral_consequence: Will works hard and sets a good impression during the day, and he has a good time at happy hour after work.

immoral_action: Will goes to a long lunch with his coworkers that takes over a couple hours, and he drinks several beers.
immoral_consequence: Will gets called into his boss's office to talk about the long lunch break and is fired when his boss smells the beer on his breath.

moral_action: Julian tells his boss that he would like to stop working overtime and gets his schedule adjusted, then goes home to tell Kristina the news.
moral_consequence: Julian is able to have a happier life/work balance and ends up being more productive.

immoral_action: Julian tells his boss he won't be coming back after today and goes home to hang out with Kristina.
immoral_consequence: Julian isn't able to pay his bills and ends up getting evicted from his apartment.

moral_action: Carl spends the morning packing the orders, then reorganizes the files after the carrier has picked up the orders.
moral_consequence: All orders are ready when the carrier drops by, and customers receive their shipments on time.

immoral_action: Carl spends half the morning reorganizing the files, then starts packing orders after lunch.
immoral_consequence: The orders are not ready for shipment when the carrier stops by at 3, so they are delayed by a day causing some customers to miss deadlines.

moral_action: Karen tells Trish that she's leaving to pick up her child and will be back in a few hours.
moral_consequence: Trish monitors the online orders while Karen is away and prepares a very large order for an important client.

immoral_action: Karen gets her things together and leaves the bakery without telling Trish that she's going.
immoral_consequence: Trish doesn't check the online orders and an important customer shows up for a very large online order that isn't prepared.

moral_action: Becca gives her two weeks notice by email and finishes the off her remaining time there.
moral_consequence: Becca's supervisor has time to find a replacement for her position.

immoral_action: Becca sends her supervisor a text message saying that she quits and does not return.
immoral_consequence: Becca's supervisor is upset for the lack of notice and will not give her a good referral.

moral_action: Fred gets a new job that is better suited for him.
moral_consequence: Fred begins to work hard every day because he doesn't want to lose his job.

immoral_action: Fred comes into the office and plays video games for an hour before starting his work.
immoral_consequence: Fred's boss notices his lack of effort and fires him.

moral_action: Paul texts his wife and asks her to go to the school and talk to the principal about their son's suspension.
moral_consequence: Paul tows six cars on his shift and even gets tipped by one of his customers.

immoral_action: Paul drives over to the school and goes in to see the principal personally.
immoral_consequence: Paul misses a number of job calls for his tow truck and gets reprimanded by his boss.

moral_action: Jennie shakes her boss's hand in thanks and orders lunch for herself and office mates for the occasion.
moral_consequence: Jennie boss keeps Jennie in mind for a promotion due to her humbleness and kindness.

immoral_action: Jennie takes a very vocal victory lap around the office while everyone watches.
immoral_consequence: Jennie's boss reprimands her for disruptive behavior and takes away the award.

moral_action: Hannah opens her email software and sends a resignation letter to her manager with two weeks notice.
moral_consequence: Hannah's manager is sad to see her go but understands and gives Hannah a glowing reference.

immoral_action: Hannah walks into her manager's office and throws her ID badge on the desk and tells the manager she's out and quits.
immoral_consequence: The manager is stressed out and scrambles to find a replacement on short notice.

moral_action: Josh tells Sarah a funny story about work.
moral_consequence: Sarah and Josh become good friends.

immoral_action: Josh makes a joke about Sarah's eczema.
immoral_consequence: Sarah leaves the break room crying.

moral_action: Pat sets his phone down to help the customers, then returns to his text conversation.
moral_consequence: Erica is appreciative of Pat helping her and doesn't mention him using his phone while working.

immoral_action: Pat ignores the growing line of customers and continues texting with his friend.
immoral_consequence: Erica makes note of Pat slacking off and writes him up for his behavior on the job.

moral_action: Carl says he thinks Kim is friendly, helpful and good for the company.
moral_consequence: Kim finds out and thinks very highly of Carl in the future.

immoral_action: Carl says he thinks Kim is stupid and looks like a dog.
immoral_consequence: Kim finds out and files a complaint against Carl, getting him fired.

moral_action: Tom respectfully says that he wished his boss decided differently, but he will work hard in the future for other promotions.
moral_consequence: Tom's boss is happy with Tom's honesty.

immoral_action: Tom yells at his boss, calling him a fool for not picking him.
immoral_consequence: Tom's boss gets mad and fires Tom on the spot.

moral_action: Carla asked her coworker nicely to take care of the spill for her.
moral_consequence: Carla's coworker cleaned up the spill and no one ended up slipping in the drink.

immoral_action: Carla yelled and belittled her coworker and told her she needed to clean up the spill.
immoral_consequence: Carla's coworker walked out on the job and Carla had to clean the mess herself.

moral_action: Sam teaches his new coworker how to get more work done.
moral_consequence: Sam's coworker learns something and doesn't feel as discouraged.

immoral_action: Sam screams at his coworker to work faster than he has been working.
immoral_consequence: Sam's coworker loses confidence and has trouble concentrating at work.

moral_action: Jill waits until the lunch break then tells her coworker the exciting gossip.
moral_consequence: Jill's coworker enjoys being in the know about the gossip and returns to work.

immoral_action: Jill goes over to her coworker while they are working and tells them about the gossip she heard.
immoral_consequence: Jill's coworker gets into trouble with the boss for gossiping when they were meant to be working.

moral_action: David jumps in to assist his coworker, lightening his workload.
moral_consequence: David's coworker is very thrilled that his coworker cares so much.

immoral_action: David runs and tells his boss that his coworker can't keep up.
immoral_consequence: David's boss comes out and yells at his coworker, making him even more stressed.

moral_action: Terry gives constructive criticism to his classmate on the art piece.
moral_consequence: Terry's classmate thanks Terry for the constructive criticism and improves his art piece.

immoral_action: Terry calls the art piece made by his classmate boring and keeps making fun of it.
immoral_consequence: Terry's classmate starts viewing Terry as an unfriendly and rude person.

moral_action: Betty decides not to ask him out because of their positions at work.
moral_consequence: Dave continues to work for Betty as an assistant with no interruptions.

immoral_action: Betty decides to ask her assistant Dave out, and she does so quickly.
immoral_consequence: Dave says yes because he thinks Betty will fire him if he says no.

moral_action: Fran spends a lot of time working nights and weekends at her job.
moral_consequence: The president of the company is impressed by Fran's hard work and gives her a promotion.

immoral_action: Fran has an affair with her boss, so he will give her a promotion.
immoral_consequence: The president of the company finds out about the affair and fires Fran.

moral_action: George sees Mika struggling to finish her work, so he goes beside her and starts unloading the rest of the goods onto the shelves.
moral_consequence: Mika is able to get her job done with George's assistance, and she feels grateful.

immoral_action: George sees Mika struggling to finish her work, but since it's not time for him to clock in, he has a cigarette outside to pass the time.
immoral_consequence: Mika is unable to complete her work on time, and she gets written up by her boss.

moral_action: Heather conditionally grants the vacation days if the employee submits a good progress report later that week.
moral_consequence: The employee works hard to make sure they can get a good report in on time and enjoys their vacation.

immoral_action: Heather says that she would grant the request but that she might have to give them a poor performance review if they take the vacation.
immoral_consequence: The employee, afraid for their job, forgoes the vacation but starts looking for another job that will allow them more vacation time.

moral_action: Dick wears a t-shirt under his shirt and loosens his tie knot at work.
moral_consequence: Dick's boss doesn't notice Dick's modifications and is just glad that Dick is at work.

immoral_action: Dick untucks his shirt and stops wearing a tie to work.
immoral_consequence: Dick's boss thinks that Dick isn't taking his job seriously enough.

moral_action: Basil tells Austin that he can do anything he sets his mind to, but he should research everything first before quitting his current job.
moral_consequence: Austin is filled with confidence and inspiration as he feels supported by his friend.

immoral_action: Basil tells Austin that it's too late to try that endeavor and that it's way too far fetched of an idea that will lead to financial ruin.
immoral_consequence: Austin is discouraged and feels silly for bringing it up as his confidence withers away.

moral_action: Michael talks to Matt about the benefits of doing things his way.
moral_consequence: Matt agrees and Michael and Matt work together to complete the project.

immoral_action: Michael thinks Matt is being stubborn and punches him to try and get him to agree.
immoral_consequence: Matt calls human resources and Michael gets fired.

moral_action: Becky looks forward to the second date since she had a memorable time.
moral_consequence: Becky has a meaningful relationship that continues through marriage.

immoral_action: Becky declines a second date because his job isn't up to her standards.
immoral_consequence: Becky has a hard time meeting anyone and is lonely frequently.

moral_action: Phil goes into his office and locks the door behind him.
moral_consequence: Phil is able to work without Terry around to bother him.

immoral_action: Phil swings a stapler at Terry's head and knocks him out cold.
immoral_consequence: Phil is called into his boss's office and is terminated from his job.

moral_action: Nicole says of course and immediately chips in and helps Ted.
moral_consequence: Ted thanks Nicole for her help and tells her that she's been a great coworker.

immoral_action: Nicole tells Ted that she managed to finish her work by herself, so he should do the same, and then leaves.
immoral_consequence: Ted ends up having to work overtime to finish his work.

moral_action: Paul puts his children in a separate stall, and showers himself in another stall.
moral_consequence: Beachgoers are spared the uncomfortable sight of watching a grown man shower with children.

immoral_action: Paul showers with his two children in view of other beachgoers.
immoral_consequence: Beachgoers disapprove but appreciate that the family does not take up three separate stalls.

moral_action: Amber leaves her son at a daycare and doesn't pick him up in the evening.
moral_consequence: Jacob comes over for dinner and is charmed by Amber's kindness, promising to visit again.

immoral_action: Amber cooks and prepares her son as a meal for dinner, giving her Jacob a full plate.
immoral_consequence: Jacob notices blood spatter in the kitchen and that the meal tastes off, then reports Amber to the police for unusual behavior.

moral_action: Sadie gets Bob's lunch to him untouched.
moral_consequence: Bob is happy to have had a visit from his friend as well as a gifted lunch.

immoral_action: Sadie promises to bring lunch to Bob at work but ends up eating it on the drive there.
immoral_consequence: Bob's lunchbreak is coming to an end and with no time to get more food, he starves for the rest of the workday.

moral_action: Fred gets his parents a kitten from a nearby neighbor.
moral_consequence: Fred's parents love the kitten and are grateful.

immoral_action: Fred gets his parents a baby raccoon that he found.
immoral_consequence: The raccoon turns feral and attacks his parents.

moral_action: Mary decides the baby should just dress nice and doesnt go overboard.
moral_consequence: The picture turns out great and the baby doesnt cry once.

immoral_action: Mary decides her baby would look better with earrings.
immoral_consequence: The baby screams and cries and has trouble sleeping for days.

moral_action: Nora cooks the kids eggs and bacon for their breakfast.
moral_consequence: The school lets Nora know that her kids have been doing really well and are focused in class.

immoral_action: Nora gives the kids handfuls of candy to eat for breakfast.
immoral_consequence: The school calls Nora and tells her she needs to pick them up because they are being disruptive.

moral_action: James looks around to try to find the mother possum.
moral_consequence: James finds the mother possum playing dead further up the path and puts the baby next to her.

immoral_action: James takes the baby possum home with him and tries to raise it as a pet.
